\name{X.entropy}
\alias{X.entropy}
\title{The information gain measure function}
\usage{
X.entropy(decisionDistrib)
}
\arguments{
  \item{decisionDistrib}{a distribution of values on the
  decision attribute.}
}
\value{
\code{qualityF}.
}
\description{
It is an auxiliary function for \code{qualityF} parameter
in the \code{\link{FS.greedy.heuristic.reduct.RST}} and
\code{\link{FS.greedy.heuristic.superreduct.RST}}
functions. It is based on \emph{entropy} as a measure of
information(Shannon, 1948).
}
\references{
C. E. Shannon, "A Mathematical Theory of Communication",
Bell System Technical Journal, vol. 27, p. 379 - 423, 623 -
656 (1948).
}

